------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Modifications by KX Systems, Inc.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Substantive modifications made by KX Systems, Inc. relative to the upstream
blueprint include (non-exhaustive):

  - KDB-X financial time-series integration via the Model Context Protocol.
  - A pluggable N-source research-agent registry
    (kxta/src/kxta/source_agents/) that generalizes the upstream
    RAG/KDB retrieval branch into an arbitrary set of data sources.
  - Borrowed data-source agents (web_search, market_data, news_headlines,
    fundamentals, sec_filings, macro_economic).
  - Source-aware query planning and LLM-chosen per-query source routing.
  - Agent-activity streaming and a convergent (fan-in) activity UI.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Vendored components
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Components under kxta/src/kxta/source_agents/_vendor/ are adapted from the
following KX Systems internal projects (faithful copies; imports rewritten and
heavy imports made lazy — no logic changes):

  - "agentic-anomaly-market-research"  (web_search, market_data,
    news_headlines, fundamentals agents and their tools)
  - "alpha-agents-strategy-miner"      (sec_filings via SEC EDGAR, and
    macro_economic via FRED)

Both source projects are owned by KX Systems, Inc.

